floorPlans.description:
Welcome to Casa Verde, North Park's newest luxury mid-rise apartments. Casa Verde offers ample amenities such as controlled access front doors, two large amenity decks with barbeques, parcel lockers, and a beautiful onsite restaurant for convenience.

Casa Verde boasts a modern, upscale design, and each available unit comes fully loaded. The one bedrooms and studios offer bright white cabinetry, beautiful countertops, stainless steel appliances, central air conditioning and heat, an in-unit washer and dryer, and large sliders for additional airflow. Every unit has a large bathroom and an ample living area perfect for entertaining.

Casa Verde is a prime location on the corner of North Park Way and Grim, giving it a 98 walk score. Within minutes, you can travel to many bars, restaurants, grocery stores, and gas stations. In one of the most desirable locations in San Diego, you have easy access to freeways, minimizing your daily commutes while also aiding to your weekend ventures.

AVAILABLE FLOOR PLANS:
1 bedroom (617 SQFT, starting at $3,150)
Studios (436 - 511 SQFT, starting at $1,995)

Residents are responsible for all utilities

Pets are welcomed with a refundable $300 security deposit and a non-refundable $50 / month pet rent. Non-aggressive breeds, 50lbs max, 2 pet max.

Call or email today for more information or to schedule a showing!

description:
Introducing CASA VERDE, North Park's tallest new apartment complex! Located just two blocks from University and 30th, this stunning building offers 436-644 sq ft studios starting at $2,195 per month and one-bedroom units from 617-700 sq ft starting at $2,850 per month.

Designed for convenience, almost everything you need is within a 2-block radius: over 20 dining spots, bars, yoga studios, gyms, salons, shops, banks, CVS, and a Mini Target with a wide range of offerings.

This 7-story architectural gem provides captivating views including downtown, the Coronado Bridge, the Pacific Ocean, Mexico, snow-covered Mt. Laguna, and Mt. Soledad. The unique layout of the smaller units separates sleeping and living areas, offering a private space for both.

Benefiting from its proximity, tenants can secure parking at the North Park garage for $40/month, which offers around 400 underutilized parking spaces just 2 blocks away.

Residents can enjoy a weekly Farmers Market, the nearby North Park Observatory, and 3rd and 7th-floor amenity spaces featuring BBQs, fire pits, lounges, and gaming areas. The 7th-floor space boasts some of San Diego's best views.

This fall, the ground floor will welcome "FINCA North Park," a new restaurant presenting a fusion of Spanish and SoCal flavors with a Tapas Restaurant, Wine Bar, and Bottle Shop.
